6. SUCCESS CRITERIA
â€¢	E2E demo on sample contracts: ingest â†’ analyze â†’ propose redlines â†’ HIL approve â†’ export â†’ (optional) anchor.
â€¢	All redlines carry rationales and citations; highâ€‘risk steps require approval.
â€¢	Immutable audit trail across edits with user/time/reason; reproducible versions.
â€¢	Zero leakage of document contents to anchoring layer (hashâ€‘only).

7. IMPLEMENTATION GUIDELINES
â€¢	Strong typing (Pydantic v2 + TypeScript); canonical DocJSON schema for contracts, clauses, and proposals.
â€¢	No confidential text in logs/traces/prompts; use content hashing and redaction where needed.
â€¢	Deterministic LangGraph nodes; checkpoint at each approval gate; idempotent retries.
â€¢	Block finalize if any asserted factual/legal reference lacks a citation or policy basis.
â€¢	Keep calculators/tooling pure and tested (caps %, survival, interest, SLA credits).
â€¢	Ship a claude.md describing tools, schemas, and safeâ€‘actions.

8. SECURITY & COMPLIANCE
â€¢	Data protection: encryption in transit and at rest; customerâ€‘managed keys (optional); secret management (KMS/Vault).
â€¢	Privacy & locality: GDPR/CCPA; data residency by tenant; retention & legal holds.
â€¢	Access: leastâ€‘privilege RBAC; fourâ€‘eyes approval for highâ€‘risk actions; full audit logs (immutable).
â€¢	Eâ€‘sign legal: ESIGN/UETA/eIDAS alignment; timestamped event trail.
â€¢	Blockchain: store only hashes and metadata; avoid personal data on chain; handle chain reorgs and provider outages.
â€¢	AppSec: OWASP ASVS, input validation, rate limiting, AV scanning on uploads; supplyâ€‘chain and dependency pinning.

